import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the overall distribution of unemployment rates?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='id', y='rate', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.axhline(y=data['rate'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['rate'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("Which region has the highest unemployment rate?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='rate', data=data)
    avg_rate = data['rate'].mean()
    plt.axvline(avg_rate, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_rate:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average unemployment rate across all regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
